complications, and how to manage these
particular respiratory viral infections.

5
00:00:24,720 --> 00:00:28,250
So RSV is an extraordinarily important
virus.

6
00:00:28,250 --> 00:00:32,160
For pediatricians and physicians who take
care of children.

7
00:00:32,160 --> 00:00:36,780
It is one of the most important viral
pathogens during the first year of life.

8
00:00:36,780 --> 00:00:40,300
It's a member of the Paramyxovirus family
of viruses and

9
00:00:40,300 --> 00:00:41,980
there's only a single serotype of RSV.

10
00:00:41,980 --> 00:00:44,510
There are two subtypes, A and B.

11
00:00:44,510 --> 00:00:46,320
But a single serotype.

12
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:51,360
These viruses are relatively labile so
when transporting from

13
00:00:51,360 --> 00:00:55,170
the patient to the laboratory, for example
trying to grow the virus and

14
00:00:55,170 --> 00:00:59,070
tissue culture, the specimens need to be
handled with care.

15
00:00:59,070 --> 00:01:01,340
The virus may be isolated in tissue
culture.

16
00:01:01,340 --> 00:01:04,380
And after incubating on the tissue culture
for.

17
